<div class="mt-20">
  <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
  <div class="my-6 w-full text-gray-700">
    <h3 class="text-black">Can I use Kindmetrics on multiple sites?</h3>
    <p> Yes! You can add as many as you like. All the sites pageviews will be counted together against your monthly pageview in your price plan.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="my-6 w-full text-gray-700">
    <h3 class="text-black">How can I start tracking?</h3>
    <p>You can easily just add an javascript to your html header. Wordpress, Ghost, Squarespace can easily add those in their system. Later documentation will be added for those. Read more how to add <a href="https://docs.kindmetrics.io/#getting-started">your tracking code here.</a></p>
  </div>
  <div class="my-6 w-full text-gray-700">
    <h3 class="text-black">Will you block me if I reach the limit?</h3>
    <p>No, we are kind! We won't block or charge for traffic spikes. If you reach over the limit two months in a row we will contact you and you can then decide if you want to upgrade or cancel your account. You will have 2 weeks. No hard feelings at all.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="my-6 w-full text-gray-700">
    <h3 class="text-black">Why isn't Kindmetrics free?</h3>
    <p>At Kindmetrics we are only selling a product. We won't sell your data or personal information. Our business model is selling an service, not data.</p>
    <p>You pay an small fee for still owning your own data. Which we think is fair.</p>
  </div>
</div>
